-- German Christmas Retail Sales May Exceed 2010, Passauer Reports
-- B y   A a r o n   K i r c h f e l d
-- 2011-12-21T04:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-21/german-christmas-retail-sales-may-exceed-2010-passauer-reports.html
Christmas retail sales in  Germany 
this year may match or slightly exceed last year’s levels,
Passauer Neue Presse reported, citing an interview with Stefan Genth, head of the country’s HDE retailer association.  Last year, sales in November and December totaled 76.8
billion euros ($100 billion) and revenue may rise 1.5 percent in
the same period of 2011, Genth told the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aaron Kirchfeld in Frankfurt at 
